<subsection xml:id="subsec-structure" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Structure</title>
  
  <introduction>
    <p>
      <term>Navigation Guide:</term> Understanding the structure and lifecycle of ideas in this collection.
    </p>
  </introduction>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-organization">
    <title>Organization</title>
    <p>
      This knowledge base is organized into several categories, each serving a different purpose:
    </p>
    <dl>
      <li>
        <title>Scribing</title>
        <p>Stable, well-integrated, long-lived synthesis. The canonical form of your knowledge.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>Eigenthoughts</title>
        <p>Atomic ideas still being formed. Provisional but curated.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>Scriber Labs</title>
        <p>Project writeups and implementations.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>Field Notes</title>
        <p>External sources: papers, books, talks, documentation.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>Practice</title>
        <p>Exercises, sketches, proofs, and drills.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <title>Meta</title>
        <p>Workflow, systems, tooling notes.</p>
      </li>
    </dl>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-note-lifecycle">
    <title>Lifecycle of Ideas</title>
    <p>
      Ideas typically flow through stages:
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li><p><term>Raw ingestion:</term> Field Notes</p></li>
      <li><p><term>Atomic exploration:</term> Eigenthoughts</p></li>
      <li><p><term>Integration:</term> Scribing chapters</p></li>
      <li><p><term>Application:</term> Practice and Labs</p></li>
    </ol>
  </subsection>

  <subsection xml:id="subsec-reading-strategies">
    <title>Reading Strategies</title>
    <p>
      This is not meant to be read linearly. Instead:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><p>Use the index to find topics of interest</p></li>
      <li><p>Follow cross-references to explore connections</p></li>
      <li><p>Visit the glossary for definitions</p></li>
      <li><p>Check Field Notes for primary sources</p></li>
    </ul>
  </subsection>

